Bugfix: Validate app archive before deleting installed app on update

We've fixed a bug where updating an app with an invalid archive produced a
misleading error and could destroy the already-installed app.
Installer::updateApp() removed the installed app before copying the new
version, without first checking that the extracted archive contained a
directory named after the app id. An archive whose top-level directory did not
match the app id therefore left the app broken. The update now validates the
archive up front, mirroring the guard in installApp(), and throws a clear
"Archive does not contain a directory named %s" error while leaving the
installed app intact.

